rComments: Jade was awesome. She is doing a PhD talking about diversity in public administration so her teaching this class about diversity was great. She gave really clear expectations and if you follow all of the grading criteria she will give you 100%. We had to do weekly discussions which could be heavy at times but they were also straightforward.

Great, caring prof HIGHLY recommend. No textbook only articles which are interesting and not long. MTs slightly long but doable if you know the material. Some questions based off of class discussion answers so go to class and pay attention!
Nice prof overall, really good looking and caring which is good cause you need to always show up to class if you're willing to succeed :)

Her lectures are very interesting and she truly cares for her students. Her exams reflected well the material seen in class and she'd always go over the essential parts of the assigned readings for the exam, so even if you hadn't read them you know what's important for the midterm. Take good notes though, because what she says can be on the exam!

Very good professor, her classes are very clear and she will let you know exactly what IS NOT on the exams. Midterms WAY too long for 1h15, most of the students did not have time to look over their answers which is quite frustrating, because the class had asked her to adjust for the second midterm. Know the material by heart to not waste time.

She was an amazing teacher. Very interesting and really nice. She wants her students to succeed. She gave the option to do a term paper if you wanted to boost your grade before the final but was not mandatory. Attendance is not mandatory although there is little information in her power point and mostly says the information during class.

She was a great prof, made the material very understandable and interesting. Take notes during class discussions as the tests will ask about them. Memorize as much as you can and you will be fine, tests were multiple choice + short answer and were completely based on lectures. Easy A with some effort!

Professeur Boivin est excellente! Elle connait très bien sa matière et s'assure de la comprehension de ces élèves. Donne des textes en ligne à lire mais fait un retour de chaque article en classe, donne beaucoup d'exemples et d'indices par rapport aux examens. Elle se soucie du succès de ses élèves et est aussi très sympathique.
